ImpossiBLE ChangeLog
====================

0.5 (2026-03-05)
-----------------

Multi-central multiplexing and iOS service-filter fidelity.

* Multiple CBCentralManager instances within a single app now work
  independently, each with its own peripheral, service, characteristic,
  and descriptor store — matching real CoreBluetooth behavior.
* Peripheral state sharing across managers: discovered services, name,
  and connection state are propagated to all CBSPeripheral instances
  for the same device UUID, emulating CoreBluetooth's shared peripheral
  objects.
* Service filter enforcement in the helper: discoverServices: UUID
  filters are now tracked and applied to results, fixing a platform
  difference where macOS CoreBluetooth returns all cached services
  regardless of the filter (iOS returns only the requested subset).
* Per-central scan-state tracking with independent service filters and
  scan options.
* retrievePeripherals: and retrieveConnectedPeripherals: swizzles that
  query across all central stores.
* L2CAP open timeout: 10-second dispatch timer fires an error callback
  if didOpenL2CAPChannel: never arrives.
* Debug -description overrides on CBSPeripheral, CBSService,
  CBSCharacteristic, and CBSDescriptor for improved logging.
* Helper now logs peripheral name alongside identifier in
  connect/disconnect events.

0.4 (2026-02-20)
-----------------

Homebrew path fix.

* Fix helper app path resolution when installed via Homebrew, where the
  impossible-helper CLI wrapper could not locate the .app bundle inside
  the Homebrew Cellar/libexec layout.

0.3 (2026-02-12)
-----------------

CLI wrapper and installation improvements.

* Add impossible-helper CLI wrapper with start/stop/restart/status
  subcommands and install/uninstall for auto-start at login via
  LaunchAgent (launchctl integration).
* Makefile: support configurable install prefix (PREFIX variable)
  for flexible installation paths.

0.2 (2026-02-03)
-----------------

Expanded CoreBluetooth coverage, descriptor support, and runtime
hardening. First tagged release.

* Full descriptor support: discover, read, and write descriptors
  (CBSDescriptor proxy, helper-side descriptor ID mapping and value
  serialization).
* Included service discovery (discoverIncludedServices:forService:).
* RSSI reading (readRSSI / didReadRSSI:error:).
* Scan deduplication and per-central scan filter logic.
* Advertisement data decoding and service UUID extraction.
* Connection event registration (registerForConnectionEvents:).
* retrievePeripherals: and retrieveConnectedPeripherals: stubs.
* Additional peripheral properties: ancsAuthorized,
  canSendWriteWithoutResponse, maximumWriteValueLengthForType:.
* Helper-side delegate coverage: didDiscoverIncludedServicesForService:,
  didDiscoverDescriptorsForCharacteristic:, didUpdateValueForDescriptor:,
  didWriteValueForDescriptor:, didModifyServices:,
  peripheralIsReadyToSendWriteWithoutResponse:,
  peripheralDidUpdateName:, willRestoreState:.
* Helper: detect client disconnects and tear down scan, peripherals,
  and L2CAP channels; handle client replacement with generation guard;
  SO_NOSIGPIPE to prevent crashes on broken pipe.
* Fix L2CAP close handshake on simulator side.
* Make codesigning optional (build succeeds unsigned with a warning if
  no matching identity is found).
* Documentation: expanded README with simulator background, 1.0 roadmap,
  single-client behavior clarification.

0.1 (2026-01-27)
-----------------

Initial release (untagged).

* Two-process architecture: library (ObjC runtime swizzling of
  CBCentralManager at +load) and native macOS helper app communicating
  over a Unix domain socket (/tmp/impossible.sock).
* Newline-delimited JSON transport with base64-encoded data payloads.
* Scanning for peripherals with optional service UUID filters.
* Connecting and disconnecting peripherals.
* Discovering services and characteristics.
* Reading and writing characteristic values (with and without response).
* Characteristic notifications (subscribe/unsubscribe).
* L2CAP channel open, read, write, and close.
* Proxy CoreBluetooth objects (CBSPeripheral, CBSService,
  CBSCharacteristic, CBSChannel) that present as real CB types.
* Delegate callbacks dispatched on the original CBCentralManager queue.
* Automatic +load activation — no setup code required; on-device builds
  compile to no-ops.
* Swift Package Manager integration, Makefile with build/install/run/
  restart/watch/clean targets, MIT license.
